explanation: This solution uses two stacks to simulate a queue. The `push` operation is O(1) because it simply appends to the `stack_newest_on_top`. The `pop` and `peek` operations are O(1) amortized because they may need to transfer all elements from `stack_newest_on_top` to `stack_oldest_on_top` in the worst case, but this happens only once every n operations. The `empty` operation is O(1) because it simply checks if both stacks are empty.

